ABOUT THE FPAC
/.header-wrap
The FPAC is a 500 seat theater, owned and operated by Regional School Unit #05, ​for the primary benefit of the schools and the communities it serves.
The Freeport Performing Arts Center (FPAC) was built as an addition to the Freeport High School opening its doors in 2003. FPAC contains a 500 seat theater, a grand lobby, backstage music room, professional sound and theatrical lighting systems.
​
The theater is managed and cared for by a professional manager, a school coordinator, and volunteers from the community to be a safe and creative high-quality space available for various performing arts uses.
The FPAC has been home to a large variety of events,
including performances put on by:
​
Casco Bay Wind Symphony
DaPonte String Quartet
Fiddle-icious
Freeport Chamber of Commerce
Freeport HS Athletics Department
Freeport Lioness Club
Freeport Players
Freeport USA - Tuba Christmas
Fusion Dance Academy
Greater Freeport Community Chorus
Italian Heritage Center Concert Band
Laura Kargul
Lighthouse Events
Maine Coast Waldorf School
Maine Senior Guide
Maine Youth Orchestra​
Michelle Lessard Dance Studio
Miss Maine Scholarship Pageant
Parnassus Films
Pine Tree Council (BSA)
Portland Jazz Orchestra
Royal River Chorus
RSU5 Performing Arts Department
Shaina's Strings
Studio for Living Arts Dance Company
Studio 48 Dance Company
University of Maine - School of Music
University of Southern Maine - School of Music
University of Southern Maine - Stonecoast MFA
University of Southern Maine - Youth Ensembles
Wescustago Youth Chorale
Women in Harmony
​​
​...and many more!
